There's no orchestra.

782
01:43:40.614 --> 01:43:42.741
Silence!

783
01:43:57.923 --> 01:44:00.967
- Rita?
- There's no band.

784
01:44:01.510 --> 01:44:03.887
Rita, wake up!

785
01:44:07.807 --> 01:44:09.434
It's okay. It's okay.

786
01:44:09.643 --> 01:44:11.645
No, it's not okay.

787
01:44:12.604 --> 01:44:14.940
What's wrong?

788
01:44:15.690 --> 01:44:18.401
Go with me somewhere.

789
01:44:19.819 --> 01:44:23.281
It's two o'clock. It's two
o'clock in the morning.

790
01:44:26.910 --> 01:44:29.955
Go with me somewhere.

791
01:44:30.163 --> 01:44:32.165
Sure.

792
01:44:32.374 --> 01:44:33.875
Now?

793
01:44:35.627 --> 01:44:37.587
Right now.

794
01:46:11.806 --> 01:46:14.809
There's no band!

795
01:46:15.685 --> 01:46:18.772
There is no band!

796
01:46:23.818 --> 01:46:25.737
This is all...

797
01:46:26.363 --> 01:46:28.782
a tape recording.

798
01:46:28.990 --> 01:46:31.952
There's no band, and yet...

799
01:46:32.786 --> 01:46:35.288
we hear a band.

800
01:46:35.789 --> 01:46:38.917
If we want to hear
a clarinet...

801
01:46:39.459 --> 01:46:41.336
listen...

802
01:46:55.016 --> 01:46:58.186
A muted trombone.

803
01:47:12.242 --> 01:47:16.079
A muted trumpet.

804
01:47:33.722 --> 01:47:36.725
It's all recorded.

805
01:47:39.144 --> 01:47:42.105
There's no band!

806
01:47:43.440 --> 01:47:45.400
It is all...

807
01:47:45.984 --> 01:47:48.361
a tape.

808
01:48:00.790 --> 01:48:05.420
It is an illusion.

809
01:48:10.217 --> 01:48:12.052
Listen!

810
01:49:25.458 --> 01:49:31.548
Ladies and gentlemen,
let Club Silencio introduce to you...

811
01:49:32.007 --> 01:49:34.759
"La Llorona de Los Angeles".

812
01:49:34.968 --> 01:49:38.180
Rebekah del Rio.

813
01:49:57.824 --> 01:50:01.244
I was all right

814
01:50:01.453 --> 01:50:04.539
For a while

815
01:50:04.748 --> 01:50:11.254
I could smile for a while

816
01:50:11.463 --> 01:50:14.883
But I saw you last night

817
01:50:15.091 --> 01:50:19.095
You held my hand so tight

818
01:50:19.304 --> 01:50:26.228
As you stopped to say hello

819
01:50:26.645 --> 01:50:31.274
You wished me well and you

820
01:50:31.483 --> 01:50:34.778
Couldn't tell

821
01:50:34.986 --> 01:50:40.659
That I've been crying

822
01:50:40.909 --> 01:50:43.870
Over you

823
01:50:44.079 --> 01:50:47.541
Crying

824
01:50:47.749 --> 01:50:50.335
Over you

825
01:50:50.877 --> 01:50:56.758
Since you said "so long"

826
01:50:57.300 --> 01:51:03.807
I've been miserable and alone

827
01:51:04.224 --> 01:51:08.103
Lonesome and crying

828
01:51:08.645 --> 01:51:11.565
Crying

829
01:51:11.982 --> 01:51:15.318
Crying

830
01:51:15.569 --> 01:51:18.071
Crying

831
01:51:18.280 --> 01:51:24.953
It's hard to understand

832
01:51:25.203 --> 01:51:31.710
That upon seeing you again

833
01:51:31.918 --> 01:51:36.173
I'd be crying

834
01:51:36.923 --> 01:51:40.051
I thought

835
01:51:40.260 --> 01:51:43.346
That I was over you

836
01:51:43.555 --> 01:51:50.520
But it's true, so true

837
01:51:50.729 --> 01:51:54.191
I love you even more

838
01:51:54.399 --> 01:51:57.944
Much more than I did before

839
01:51:58.153 --> 01:52:04.034
But darling, what can I do

840
01:52:04.242 --> 01:52:10.081
You don't love me anymore

841
01:52:10.332 --> 01:52:17.255
And I will always be

842
01:52:17.839 --> 01:52:24.429
Crying over you

843
01:52:24.638 --> 01:52:30.727
Crying over you

844
01:52:30.936 --> 01:52:37.234
Your love has captured

845
01:52:37.442 --> 01:52:43.240
The whole of my heart

846
01:52:43.490 --> 01:52:47.244
That was left crying

847
01:52:47.452 --> 01:52:50.705
Crying

848
01:52:50.914 --> 01:52:54.084
Crying

849
01:52:54.292 --> 01:52:57.754
Crying

850
01:54:18.460 --> 01:54:20.545
Betty?

851
01:54:23.548 --> 01:54:25.300
Betty?

852
01:54:37.354 --> 01:54:40.190
Where are you?

853
01:57:23.311 --> 01:57:25.146
Hey, pretty girl.

854
01:57:26.106 --> 01:57:28.066
Time to wake up.

855
01:59:05.163 --> 01:59:08.250
- Where have you been?
- What do you want?

856
01:59:08.917 --> 01:59:11.837
My lamp and dishes.

857
01:59:13.672 --> 01:59:16.591
Come on, Diane,
it's been three weeks.

858
01:59:18.969 --> 01:59:22.055
I put your dishes in that box.

859
01:59:41.992 --> 01:59:45.620
- That's my ashtray.
- Take it.

860
01:59:57.424 --> 02:00:01.761
- Anytime.
- I'm just making sure, Diane.

861
02:00:11.146 --> 02:00:13.315
This is it?

862
02:00:18.904 --> 02:00:22.449
By the way, those two detectives
came by again looking for you.

863
02:01:16.419 --> 02:01:18.547
Camilla!

864
02:01:21.132 --> 02:01:23.426
You've come back.

865
02:03:04.861 --> 02:03:07.864
What was that you were saying,
beautiful?

866
02:03:08.406 --> 02:03:10.158
I said...

867
02:03:10.617 --> 02:03:13.370
you drive me wild.

868
02:03:25.924 --> 02:03:28.343
We shouldn't do this anymore.

869
02:03:34.724 --> 02:03:37.102
Don't say that.

870
02:03:41.773 --> 02:03:44.693
Don't ever say that.

871
02:03:44.943 --> 02:03:46.820
Don't, Diane!

872
02:03:47.028 --> 02:03:48.488
Stop it!

873
02:03:48.697 --> 02:03:50.365
Diane, stop!

874
02:03:51.533 --> 02:03:54.244
I've tried to tell you this before.

875
02:04:02.752 --> 02:04:05.005
It's him, isn't it?

876
02:04:16.600 --> 02:04:19.895
I'm not trying to show you how
to do the scene, but just...

877
02:04:21.146 --> 02:04:24.191
watch me and I think you'll
understand what I'm getting at.

878
02:04:28.695 --> 02:04:31.990
Don't sit so rigid, just...

879
02:04:32.199 --> 02:04:33.700
just relax.

880
02:04:34.576 --> 02:04:38.705
Now, the two of you are alone
and it's real comfortable.

881
02:04:40.332 --> 02:04:43.001
Like you've known
each other forever.

882
02:04:43.210 --> 02:04:46.505
Even if you don't say anything,
it's real comfortable.

883
02:04:48.215 --> 02:04:51.676
Hank, can you just clear the set?
There's too many people around here.

884
02:04:51.885 --> 02:04:54.804
- Let's get this worked out.
- Clear the set!

885
02:04:55.013 --> 02:04:57.599
Everyone have a cup of coffee.

886
02:04:58.642 --> 02:05:01.895
- Everyone, please!
- Can Diane stay?

887
02:05:02.145 --> 02:05:05.690
Yeah, sure, Diane can stay.
Hank, let Diane stay!

888
02:05:05.899 --> 02:05:07.692
Diane!

889
02:05:13.073 --> 02:05:16.451
Now, when she starts to cry,
don't pull her towards you.

890
02:05:18.578 --> 02:05:23.416
Let her fall into you.
Just let her fall.

891
02:05:27.379 --> 02:05:29.464
And when you kiss her...

892
02:05:31.007 --> 02:05:34.010
it's just a continuation
of that move.

893
02:05:36.388 --> 02:05:38.473
There's no break.

894
02:06:03.415 --> 02:06:05.625
Kill the lights!

895
02:06:16.011 --> 02:06:18.763
Don't be mad.
Don't make it be like this.

896
02:06:18.972 --> 02:06:22.642
Oh, sure, you want me to make
this easy for you.

897
02:06:22.851 --> 02:06:25.687
No fucking way!
It's not gonna be!

898
02:06:26.479 --> 02:06:29.024
- It's not easy for me!
- Diane!

899
02:07:53.149 --> 02:07:56.403
Hello, it's me.
Leave a message.

900
02:07:59.114 --> 02:08:00.866
Diane?

901
02:08:05.412 --> 02:08:08.331
- Hello?
- Diane?

902
02:08:09.916 --> 02:08:11.334
Camilla.

903
02:08:11.543 --> 02:08:15.422
Diane, the car's waiting.
Are you okay?

904
02:08:16.381 --> 02:08:18.633
You coming?

905
02:08:24.097 --> 02:08:28.393
Good. It means so much to me.

906
02:08:29.102 --> 02:08:32.772
Go on. The car's right
outside your house.

907
02:08:33.190 --> 02:08:35.984
It's been waiting, okay?

908
02:08:40.238 --> 02:08:42.073
Okay.

909
02:08:42.282 --> 02:08:46.244
It's 6980, Mulholland Drive.

910
02:08:47.162 --> 02:08:49.372
Mulholland Drive.

911
02:09:58.775 --> 02:10:02.153
What are you doing?
We don't stop here.

912
02:10:07.033 --> 02:10:09.077
A surprise.

913
02:10:32.017 --> 02:10:33.852
Shortcut.

914
02:10:36.438 --> 02:10:38.940
Come on, sweetheart.

915
02:10:44.279 --> 02:10:46.198
It's beautiful.

916
02:10:46.406 --> 02:10:48.742
A secret path.

917
02:11:56.476 --> 02:11:58.645
Perfect timing.

918
02:11:59.354 --> 02:12:01.481
Welcome, Diane.

919
02:12:07.112 --> 02:12:10.657
Well...
Here's to love.

920
02:12:21.209 --> 02:12:24.045
Here's to love.

921
02:12:28.800 --> 02:12:30.969
Here she is!

922
02:12:39.519 --> 02:12:42.397
I don't believe
you met my mother.

923
02:12:43.064 --> 02:12:45.525
Hi. I'm Diane Selwyn.

924
02:12:45.734 --> 02:12:49.404
Just call me Coco, everybody
does. Pleased to meet you.

925
02:12:49.779 --> 02:12:52.699
Well, let's eat!
I'm starving!

926
02:12:59.039 --> 02:13:01.166
I'm sorry I was late.

927
02:13:21.603 --> 02:13:24.231
I'm from Deep River, Ontario.

928
02:13:24.814 --> 02:13:28.568
- A small town.
- So you rolled in here from Canada.

929
02:13:31.446 --> 02:13:34.241
I always wanted to come here.

930
02:13:35.033 --> 02:13:38.203
I won this jitterbug contest.

931
02:13:38.912 --> 02:13:42.082
That sort of led to acting.

932
02:13:42.666 --> 02:13:46.086
You know, wanting to act.

933
02:13:46.795 --> 02:13:49.256
When my aunt died...

934
02:13:50.465 --> 02:13:53.385
Anyway, she left me some money.

935
02:13:54.135 --> 02:13:56.847
- She worked here.
- In the movies?

936
02:13:57.973 --> 02:13:59.349
Yes.

937
02:14:00.809 --> 02:14:03.144
How did you meet Camilla?

938
02:14:04.938 --> 02:14:08.775
- On the "Sylvia North Story".
- Camilla was great in that.

939
02:14:08.984 --> 02:14:11.945
I never went to
Casablanca with Luigi.

940
02:14:12.153 --> 02:14:14.781
- What a pity!
- Then go!

941
02:14:24.416 --> 02:14:27.335
I wanted the lead so bad.

942
02:14:28.753 --> 02:14:32.174
Anyway, Camilla got the part.

943
02:14:35.302 --> 02:14:37.220
The director...

944
02:14:37.470 --> 02:14:39.389
Bob Rooker?

945
02:14:39.598 --> 02:14:41.391
Yes.

946
02:14:43.935 --> 02:14:46.730
He didn't think so much of me.

947
02:14:50.901 --> 02:14:53.778
Anyway, that's when
we became friends.

948
02:14:55.322 --> 02:14:56.907
She helped me...

949
02:14:57.407 --> 02:15:00.535
getting some parts in some
of her films.

950
02:15:02.871 --> 02:15:04.915
I see.

951
02:15:19.763 --> 02:15:23.934
So I got the pool,
and she got the pool man.

952
02:15:26.311 --> 02:15:30.232
I couldn't believe it. I wanted
to buy that judge a Rolls Royce.

953
02:15:36.863 --> 02:15:39.616
Sometimes, good things happen.

954
02:16:33.336 --> 02:16:36.047
So I guess we've saved
the best for last.

955
02:16:39.509 --> 02:16:42.929
- Do you want to tell them?
- No, you tell them.

956
02:16:46.683 --> 02:16:49.102
Camilla and I...

957
02:17:01.239 --> 02:17:03.074
are going to be...

958
02:17:15.670 --> 02:17:17.714
Sorry about that.

959
02:17:25.180 --> 02:17:27.307
No, I'm fine.

960
02:17:33.021 --> 02:17:35.607
This is the girl.

961
02:17:36.608 --> 02:17:39.528
Don't show me this
fucking thing here.

962
02:17:40.237 --> 02:17:43.490
It's just an actress' photo
resume. Everybody's got one.

963
02:17:45.116 --> 02:17:47.536
You got the money?

964
02:17:47.744 --> 02:17:49.830
I sure do.

965
02:18:01.049 --> 02:18:04.761
Okay, now, once you hand that over
to me, it's a done deal.

966
02:18:08.181 --> 02:18:10.725
You sure you want this?

967
02:18:15.564 --> 02:18:18.483
More than anything in this world.

968
02:18:29.077 --> 02:18:32.122
When it's finished, you'll find
this where I told you.

969
02:18:45.927 --> 02:18:48.722
What's it open?

970
02:23:13.486 --> 02:23:15.989
Silencio.
